We are a growing HR team in a high-growth Software as a Service (SaaS) company. In this role, you would be responsible for assisting with the administration of benefits and retirement programs, including medical, dental, vision, life and disability insurance, and 401(k) plans.\n\nThis is a remote eligible position and you may work remotely from anywhere in the US where Smartsheet is registered.\n\nYou Will:\n• Lead benefit programs, including but not limited to compliance and administration\n• Perform frequent audits of benefits-related data, identifying process breakdowns and ensure the accuracy of the HRIS (Workday) and other vendor systems\n• Manage employee inquiries regarding benefits enrollments, changes, escalations, and general questions while providing a positive customer service experience\n• Support relationships with vendors and brokers, including new and existing service agreements in partnership with internal Procurement and Legal teams\n• Drive consistent project management support for annual benefit activities such as open enrollment, renewals, and plan audits; as well as cross functional programs\n• Report on utilization, cost, and other notable trends for varying levels of leadership\n• Analyze market trends and compare to our current offerings to ensure we remain competitive\n• Partner with internal HR Operations, Payroll, and People Analytics teams ensuring benefits administration is delivered consistently\n\nYou Have:\n• Bachelor’s degree in Psychology, Human Resources, Business Administration or related field or equivalent years of relatable Human Resources experience\n• 3+ years of comparable benefit experience with an emphasis 401k administration and auditing\n• Experience using Google for Work, Smartsheet, and Workday preferred\n• Experience with Costa Rican and Australian benefits is a plus\n• Strong attention to detail and accuracy for excellent organization of audits and overall data management\n• Experience working on confidential programs with access to sensitive information\n• Exceptional written and oral communication skills, including formal presentations to different levels of leadership\n• Capacity to be flexible and adapt quickly to shifting priorities as well as experience working cross functionally and collaborating with internal and external stakeholders\n• Ability to work independently and apply analytical and problem solving skills to deliver excellent results\n\nPerks \u0026 Benefits:\n• HSA, 100% employer-paid premiums, or buy-up medical/vision and dental coverage options for full-time employees\n• Equity - Restricted Stock Units (RSUs) with all offers\n• Lucrative Employee Stock Purchase Program (15% discount)\n• 401k Match to help you save for your future (50% of your contribution up to the first 6% of your eligible pay)\n• Monthly stipend to support your work and productivity\n• Flexible Time Away Program, plus Incidental Sick Leave\n• US employees are automatically covered under Smartsheet-sponsored life insurance, short-term, and long-term disability plans\n• US employees receive 12 paid holidays per year\n• Up to 24 weeks of Parental Leave\n• Personal paid Volunteer Day to support our community\n• Opportunities for professional growth and development including access to LinkedIn Learning online courses\n• Company Funded Perks, including a counseling membership, local retail discounts, and your own personal Smartsheet account\n• Teleworking options from any registered location in the U.S. (role specific)\n\nSmartsheet provides a competitive range of compensation for roles that may be hired in different geographic areas we are licensed to operate our business from. Actual compensation is determined by several factors including, but not limited to, level of professional, educational experience, skills, and specific candidate location. In addition, this role will be eligible for a market competitive bonus and RSU stock grant upon accepted offer. Our virtual, phone, and mail audits are conducted nationwide, while our physical audits are focused in the Southwest region of the US.\n\nRole Description\n\nThis is a full-time remote role for a Phone Premium Auditor. The Phone Premium Auditor will be responsible for conducting insurance audits over the phone, reviewing financial records, analyzing insurance data, and ensuring accuracy and compliance with industry standards. Since 2015, our vetted, diverse, expert teachers have taught over 1.5 million learners and earned more than $488 million teaching on Outschool.\n\nWhy teach on Outschool?\n• Connect with our network of 1.5M+ all-time enrolled learners\n• Set your own prices and schedule as an Independent Contractor (IC)\n• Offer small online group classes, 1-1 virtual instruction, and/or create self-paced offerings\n• Low administrative burden (Outschool makes it easy to teach online)\n• Simple online application process to get started\n\nWhat we look for in our teachers:\n\nOutschool does not require formal teaching credentials to teach on the platform. We believe that many adults can offer quality learning experiences based on their expertise and interests. We do, however, have several requirements, detailed below. Teachers need to fulfill these requirements to become and to remain a teacher on Outschool:\n• You must be at least 18 years old.\n• You must reside full-time in any of the 50 United States, Mexico, Canada, Australia, New Zealand, South Korea, and the United Kingdom (note that U.S. territories do not apply at this time).\n• You must have the ability to receive PayPal payments.\n• You must have one or more expertise or passion that you will base your classes around.\n• You must meet our community standards, including prompt, professional communication with families and the Outschool team.\n• You must observe our class content policy, including the policy that Outschool classes are secular and objective.\n• You must have a reliable and fast Internet connection (over 3Mbps upload and download).\n• You must have the technical know-how to effectively run online classes.\n• You must have a good command of written and spoken English.\n• You must verify your identity and pass a criminal background check\n\nPlease note: Teachers on Outschool are independent contractors with their own teaching styles, methods and materials. except in South Dakota, Vermont and West Virginia.\n\nThe annual base salary for this position ranges from $199,200.00 in our lowest geographic market to $471,100.00 in our highest geographic market. Actual salary will vary based on a candidate's location, qualifications, skills and experience.\n\nInformation about benefits can be found here.\n\nWHO WE ARE LOOKING FOR\n\nWe are seeking a visionary leader to spearhead CPI’s Advanced Machine Learning initiatives, aimed at revolutionizing Nike’s product creation lifecycle—from ideation through to supply chain. This role requires a deep learning expert who is well-versed in generative AI advancements and capable of guiding cutting-edge research in these domains. This leader will build and develop the team, shape the science philosophy, plan, and strategize, as we explore domains such as Large Language Models (LLMs), diffusion models, reinforcement learning (RL) and simulation to support new experiences for our designers and developers.\n\nWHAT YOU WILL WORK ON\n\nDesign Acceleration: Al generated - Image and video generation, text and content creation to augment and enhance designer experience\n\nML Optimization: Adding LLM's to the existing data models to enhance accuracy of off the shelf GenAl solutions customized to Nike's data set and business needs.\n\nWHO YOU WILL WORK WITH\n\nThis role reports to the VP of Consumer Product and Innovation and will work closely with Product creation, Merch, Design, Innovation teams, and key partners across Footwear, Apparel, Ops, Merch and Geos.\n\nWHAT YOU BRING\n• Bachelor’s Degree in computer science, statistics, mathematics, software engineering, or related field (Master's or Ph.D. preferred).\n• Experienced leader of leaders, with 10 years of experience leading multiple science and engineering teams.\n• At least 15 years of experience in building and applying ML models to solve complex, large-scale problems.\n• Has a strong understanding of foundational models including large language models across multiple modalities, reinforcement learning, supervised learning, and other cutting-edge techniques in generative Al.\n• Proven track record of leading seasoned scientists and developing junior talent.\n• Proficient in one or more programming languages with strong technical skills.\n• Exceptional verbal and written communication skills, capable of advocating technical solutions to both technical and business audiences.\n• Publications in top-tier conferences or journals.\n\nWe are committed to fostering a diverse and inclusive environment for all employees and job applicants. We offer a number of accommodations to complete our interview process including screen readers, sign language interpreters, accessible and single location for in-person interviews, closed captioning, and other reasonable modifications as needed. Primary responsibility is to maintain and grow the revenue stream through renewal management, cross-sell and up-sell of new opportunities.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eEssential Key Responsibilities\u003cbr\u003e• Fulfill the role of trusted advisor on Dun \u0026amp; Bradstreet solutions through the development of strong, positive relationships with clients\u003cbr\u003e• Ability to prospect, qualify, and process leads from various lead generation sources\u003cbr\u003e• Develop and maintain an active pipeline of forecasted sales to meet annual quota objectives\u003cbr\u003e• Grow the revenue stream by identifying new logo opportunities, win-back opportunities and close cross-sell opportunities\u003cbr\u003e• Effectively and powerfully communicate the value proposition to prospective customers through a consultative process to ensure the majority convert to customers\u003cbr\u003e• Maintain consistent and accurate data in SFDC to support territory, account planning and forecasting\u003cbr\u003e• This role is intended for an entry level professional with limited prior experience\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eEducation and Experience\u003cbr\u003e• Bachelor’s Degree: Required\u003cbr\u003e• Years of Relevant Experience: 2 to 4 years\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eEssential Skills and/or Certifications\u003cbr\u003e• Minimum of two (2) years of high-value, business-to-business, solution sales experience\u003cbr\u003e• Proven success in new customer acquisition\u003cbr\u003e• Highly driven, focused and committed with a proven track record of consistent sales achievement\u003cbr\u003e• Proven ability to work independently as well as a member of a team with flexibility to adapt and manage change effective in an ever-changing environment\u003cbr\u003e• Ability to manage and report on opportunities throughout the various stages within the sales pipeline. Salesforce expertise a plus\u003cbr\u003e• Ability to operate in a high velocity, metrics driven sales organization\u003cbr\u003e• Positive “can do” attitude, sense of urgency and strong desire to be successful\u003cbr\u003e• Strong phone presence with active listening, negotiation and closing skills\u003cbr\u003e• Excellent verbal and written communications skills\u003cbr\u003e• Show an ownership mindset in everything you do; be a problem solver, be curious and be inspired to take action, be proactive, seek ways to collaborate and connect with people and teams in support of driving success\u003cbr\u003e• Continuous growth mindset, keep learning through social experiences and relationships with stakeholder, experts, colleagues and mentors as well as widen and broaden your competencies through structural courses and programs\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eKey Stakeholders\u003cbr\u003e• External Clients, Pre-sales, Client Success, Marketing, Data, Product, Delivery and Customer Service Team members\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eBenefits We Offer\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e· Generous paid time off in your first year, increasing with tenure.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e· Up to 16 weeks 100% paid parental leave after one year of employment.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e· Paid sick time to care for yourself or family members.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e· Education assistance and extensive training resources.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e· Do Good Program: Paid volunteer days \u0026amp; donation matching.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e· Competitive 401k \u0026amp; Employee Stock Purchase Plan with company matching.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e· Health \u0026amp; wellness benefits, including discounted Wellhub membership rates.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e· Medical, dental \u0026amp; vision insurance for you, spouse/partner \u0026amp; dependents.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e· Learn more about our benefits: http://bit.ly/41Yyc3d.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eAll Dun \u0026amp; Bradstreet job postings can be found at https://www.dnb.com/about-us/careers-and-people/joblistings.html and https://jobs.lever.co/dnb. ago",[[[null,null,"paid_time_off",3],[null,null,"health_insurance",1]],["paid_time_off","health_insurance"]],"",0,null,null,["0","512DA8","FFFFFF"],"Who Are We? Taking care of our customers, our communities and each other. That’s the Travelers Promise. By honoring this commitment, we have maintained our reputation as one of the best property casualty insurers in the industry for over 160 years. Join us to discover a culture that is rooted in innovation and thrives on collaboration. Imagine loving what you do and where you do it. Job Category Corporate Services/Other Compensation Overview The annual base salary range provided for this position is a nationwide market range and represents a broad range of salaries for this role across the country. The actual salary for this position will be determined by a number of factors, including the scope, complexity and location of the role; the skills, education, training, credentials and experience of the candidate; and other conditions of employment. As part of our comprehensive compensation and benefits program, employees are also eligible for performance-based cash incentive awards. Salary Range $101,300.00 - $167,000.00 Target Openings 1 What Is the Opportunity? The Manager, Corporate Real Estate directs corporate real estate activities within an assigned portfolio. Supports business operations through the delivery of real estate solutions at optimal cost. Responsibilities include: • Negotiating of leases for the establishment, renewal, termination, subleasing, expansion, downsizing, and/or relocation of field offices over a geographically diverse portfolio. • Management of all aspects of interior design, tenant construction, furniture installation and move-in activities involving new or existing facilities, as assigned. Requires extensive personal interaction with business unit leadership, as well as third party service providers. What Will You Do? Determines office space requirements based on staffing projections and business plans. Oversees brokers and does market research to identify suitable office locations. Analyzes financial, demographic, and suitability aspects of available alternative sites. With assistance, prepares suitable presentation materials and presents alternatives to appropriate management staff. Prepares final recommendation narrative and financial analysis of alternative sites to management. Utilizes independent decision-making skills to negotiate lease terms, document language, and related issues to obtain the most favorable agreement available for the corporation. Utilizes appropriate resource personnel, including broker and legal support, as needed. Supports Facility Management operations. Oversees day-to-day facilities outsourced providers Supports third-party facility and project management staff involved with the design, construction, and move activities, as assigned. Helps to manage the leasing schedule and budget process to provide optimal cost savings for the organization. Identifies opportunities to reduce unneeded space and manages the disposition process of same. Collaborates with peers in other departments such as IT, Legal, Human Resources, Security, etc. as needed to perform facility, leasing and project management responsibilities. Assists leadership with reporting and other projects, as assigned. Supports the Operational Response Team as necessary during crisis management events. Conducts moderately complex financial/business analysis including the preparation of financial presentations. Perform other duties as assigned. What Will Our Ideal Candidate Have? Bachelor's degree with concentration in business administration, real estate, finance or related field preferred. Demonstrated ability to forecast and prepare budgets. General knowledge of financial terms and principles. Intermediate analytical skills, oral and written communication skills. What is a Must Have? Minimum 5 years’ experience in Commercial Real Estate, Facilities Management or related field required. 2+ years’ experience in, or exposure to, the disciplines of Real Estate and Real Estate Law, Space Planning, or Facilities/Property Management is required. What Is in It for You? Health Insurance: Employees and their eligible family members – including spouses, domestic partners, and children – are eligible for coverage from the first day of employment. Retirement: Travelers matches your 401(k) contributions dollar-for-dollar up to your first 5% of eligible pay, subject to an annual maximum. If you have student loan debt, you can enroll in the Paying it Forward Savings Program. When you make a payment toward your student loan, Travelers will make an annual contribution into your 401(k) account. You are also eligible for a Pension Plan that is 100% funded by Travelers. Paid Time Off: Start your career at Travelers with a minimum of 20 days Paid Time Off annually, plus nine paid company Holidays. Wellness Program: The Travelers wellness program is comprised of tools, discounts and resources that empower you to achieve your wellness goals and caregiving needs. In addition, our mental health program provides access to free professional counseling services, health coaching and other resources to support your daily life needs. Volunteer Encouragement: We have a deep commitment to the communities we serve and encourage our employees to get involved. Travelers has a Matching Gift and Volunteer Rewards program that enables you to give back to the charity of your choice. Employment Practices Travelers is an equal opportunity employer. The actual salary for this position will be determined by a number of factors, including the scope, complexity and location of the role; the skills, education, training, credentials and experience of the candidate; and other conditions of employment. As part of our comprehensive compensation and benefits program, employees are also eligible for performance-based cash incentive awards. Salary Range $101,300.00 - $167,000.00 Target Openings 1 What Is the Opportunity? The Manager, Corporate Real Estate directs corporate real estate activities within an assigned portfolio. Supports business operations through the delivery of real estate solutions at optimal cost. Responsibilities include: • Negotiating of leases for the establishment, renewal, termination, subleasing, expansion, downsizing, and/or relocation of field offices over a geographically diverse portfolio. • Management of all aspects of interior design, tenant construction, furniture installation and move-in activities involving new or existing facilities, as assigned. Requires extensive personal interaction with business unit leadership, as well as third party service providers. What Will You Do? Determines office space requirements based on staffing projections and business plans. Oversees brokers and does market research to identify suitable office locations. Analyzes financial, demographic, and suitability aspects of available alternative sites. With assistance, prepares suitable presentation materials and presents alternatives to appropriate management staff. Prepares final recommendation narrative and financial analysis of alternative sites to management. Utilizes independent decision-making skills to negotiate lease terms, document language, and related issues to obtain the most favorable agreement available for the corporation. Utilizes appropriate resource personnel, including broker and legal support, as needed. Supports Facility Management operations. Oversees day-to-day facilities outsourced providers Supports third-party facility and project management staff involved with the design, construction, and move activities, as assigned. Helps to manage the leasing schedule and budget process to provide optimal cost savings for the organization. Identifies opportunities to reduce unneeded space and manages the disposition process of same. Collaborates with peers in other departments such as IT, Legal, Human Resources, Security, etc. as needed to perform facility, leasing and project management responsibilities. Assists leadership with reporting and other projects, as assigned. Supports the Operational Response Team as necessary during crisis management events. Conducts moderately complex financial/business analysis including the preparation of financial presentations. Perform other duties as assigned. What Will Our Ideal Candidate Have? Bachelor\u0026#39;s degree with concentration in business administration, real estate, finance or related field preferred. Demonstrated ability to forecast and prepare budgets. General knowledge of financial terms and principles. Intermediate analytical skills, oral and written communication skills. What is a Must Have? Minimum 5 years’ experience in Commercial Real Estate, Facilities Management or related field required. 2+ years’ experience in, or exposure to, the disciplines of Real Estate and Real Estate Law, Space Planning, or Facilities/Property Management is required. What Is in It for You? Health Insurance: Employees and their eligible family members – including spouses, domestic partners, and children – are eligible for coverage from the first day of employment. Retirement: Travelers matches your 401(k) contributions dollar-for-dollar up to your first 5% of eligible pay, subject to an annual maximum. If you have student loan debt, you can enroll in the Paying it Forward Savings Program. When you make a payment toward your student loan, Travelers will make an annual contribution into your 401(k) account. You are also eligible for a Pension Plan that is 100% funded by Travelers. Paid Time Off: Start your career at Travelers with a minimum of 20 days Paid Time Off annually, plus nine paid company Holidays. Wellness Program: The Travelers wellness program is comprised of tools, discounts and resources that empower you to achieve your wellness goals and caregiving needs. In addition, our mental health program provides access to free professional counseling services, health coaching and other resources to support your daily life needs.
